<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4680] FSUtils.isInSafeMode() checks should operate on HBase root dir, where we have permissions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4680</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The HDFS safe mode check workaround introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4510&quot; title=&quot;Check and workaround usage of internal HDFS APIs in HBase&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4510&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4510&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; performs a &lt;tt&gt;FileSystem.setPermission()&lt;/tt&gt; operation on the root directory (&quot;/&quot;) when attempting to trigger a &lt;tt&gt;SafeModeException&lt;/tt&gt;.  As a result, it requires superuser privileges when running with DFS permission checking enabled.  Changing the operations to act on the HBase root directory should be safe, since the master process must have write access to it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
