                            <comment id="13139915" author="qwertymaniac" created="Mon, 31 Oct 2011 04:54:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I apologize for missing the whole activity on this (didn&apos;t see a comment on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4510&quot; title=&quot;Check and workaround usage of internal HDFS APIs in HBase&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4510&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4510&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, oops).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think a better fix would have been to just catch other exceptions (which is something I missed despite commenting).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This change is fine too, but has lead to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4705&quot; title=&quot;HBase won&amp;#39;t initialize if /hbase is not present&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4705&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4705&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; scenarios. Could we revert this and instead add a:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (Safemode) {
 &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
} &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (Others) {
 ignore;
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Kinda block, while still operating on the only dir guaranteed to exist (/ - root)?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
